			<div class="content" id="post-content-4802583">
									

<p>Thank you ever so! It's only due to the foresight of my kind critters that the latter half is as grounded as it is - it was originally even more abstract!</p>
<p>But given how abstract the themes are, it was something I was having issues with, keeping everything realistic and easy to track. It's not easy to make literal the slow and methodical destruction of someone's happiness!</p>
<p>I will say that the Croquembouche segment works on a literal and abstract level, and that figure stuck in the quagmire is identified in the piece!</p>

