					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/grigori-karpin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4558017); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4558017&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204538" alt="Grigori Karpin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4558017)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/grigori-karpin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4558017); return false;" >Grigori Karpin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1603521869 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Oct 2020 06:44</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4802854">
									

<p>This is far too close to the contest entry upon which is cribs the formatting, so much so that I would assume it would not exist if not for the contest entry. Now, being inspired by something else is part of the creative process&#8230; but this is not inspiration. The plot, the style of writing, even the character feels too much like the entry from Crom.</p>
<p>The opening splash could be the same article, in that the wording is so similar. I realize many actual reviews are worded in a similar manner&#8230; but this isn’t an actual review, it’s a piece of fiction.</p>
<p>There’s even a bit about a sausage roll cart, which I’m fairly sure is also a plot point in the entry. I do not begrudge anyone from enjoying this but I felt like this was an attempt to recreate another article in slightly different fashion. And as such, it is not for me.</p>
<p>-1</p>

							</div>

								
