			<div class="content" id="post-content-4803133">
									

<p>I'm sorry you felt that way! It's something I went back and forth on alot while writing, but ultimately determined the differences where great enough.</p>
<p>The endpoint of both stories is similar! That I can't deny - &quot;broken person returns home&quot;. But the reasons for this and the journey that they have taken to get there couldn't be more different - Eden saw the center of the universe and had her soul stolen. Sam looked back at a life long lived and could not handle what they had seen.</p>
<p>I would be remiss if I didn't point at least one thing out though - the formatting is the Inkblot 9 theme (<a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/theme:inkblot">http://www.scpwiki.com/theme:inkblot</a>), which was intended by Croquembouche to be a refresh of the Ambrose GoI format. So&#8230; Yes, the formatting and structural framing of &quot;food critic review&quot; are very similar, as self-similar as any two GoI formats are.</p>

							</div>

								
					
